-- UBS Appoints Heller to Head Gaming, Leisure Investment Banking in Americas
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   K e e h n e r   a n d   B e t h   J i n k s
-- 2010-10-22T19:56:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/ubs-appoints-heller-to-head-gaming-leisure-investment-banking-in-americas.html
UBS AG , the biggest Swiss bank,
hired Rob Heller to head gaming and leisure investment banking
in the Americas.  Heller will join as a managing director in New York, UBS
said today in an internal memo obtained by Bloomberg News and
confirmed by  Doug Morris , a spokesman for the bank in New York.
Heller will report to  Jackson  Hsieh, head of real estate,
lodging and leisure banking at UBS.  He was previously president of Heller Gaming & Leisure, an
advisory firm and boutique investment bank. Heller replaces
 William Newby , who joined Jefferies Group Inc. as head of gaming
investment banking this month.  Heller also previously worked at Salomon Brothers, Lehman
Brothers Holdings Inc. and Bear Stearns Cos., according to the
memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
